FILE: Medical technology students work in a laboratory. AFP/Jam Sta Rosa JOHANNESBURG - South Africa records 4,379 new COVID-19 infections in the last 24 hours. The Western Cape is now the country's epicentre with 1,181 new cases. Gauteng and Kwa-Zulu Natal mirrored each other with over 900 cases recorded READ: COVID-19 in SA | 9,818 new cases, 53 deaths While the Eastern Cape reported 465 new infections. The positivity rate stands at 23.1 percent. A further 30 COVID-19 related deaths have been recorded. Bringing the death toll to 91,228.